          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1676975664681-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4] </span>knobs of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and <strong>remaining garlic</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until slightly softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>Chantenay carrots</strong> (no need to top or peel!) with 120ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml] </span><strong>reserved potato water</strong> and cook, covered for an initial 8-9 min or until tender with a slight bite</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1676975669803-x200.jpg",
