          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1676975669803-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the carrots have had an initial 8-9 min, add the <strong>chopped cavolo nero </strong>and cook, covered for a final 2-3 min or until wilted – these are your <strong>Chantenay carrots & greens</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>cornflour </strong>and<strong> soy sauce </strong>to the reserved small bowl with the <strong>remaining beef stock mix </strong>and gradually stir in<strong> </strong>130ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]<strong> </span>boiled water </strong>(this is to ensure there's no lumps!) – this is your <strong>gravy mix</strong></p><p>Put the <strong>gravy mix</strong> in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 2 min or until thickened, stirring half way – this is your <strong>gravy</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1676975673272-x200.jpg",
